    <p>Adrenal lesions are usually metastases from distant organ malignites<xref ref-type="bibr" rid="ref1">1</xref>. The most common metastases arise from bronchial carcinomas. Primary adrenal lymphoma is rare<xref ref-type="bibr" rid="ref2">2</xref> and adrenal lymphomas are usually bilateral<xref ref-type="bibr" rid="ref3">3</xref>.</p>
